<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="584" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,469,151,211]" box="[151,469,151,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,469,151,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="584" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,469,151,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">
<taxonomicName box="[151,368,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridenta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,368,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">Sophonia tridenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[375,469,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,469,151,211]" box="[151,414,186,211]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">(Figs. 14, 29,44,53–59)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="585" pageId="7" pageNumber="584" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,258,499]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">Vertex pale yellow with apical ovalblack spot and two median longitudinal linesfused near hindmargin, continued on pronotum and scutellum as median stripe. Forewing yellowish, with dark brown stripe along anal margin rarely reaching apex of clavus, claval apex brown; costal margin with anterior, oblique and two posterior transverseblack fasciae; second apical cell with black spot (Figs. 14, 29 &amp; 44).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,258,499]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">
Head bluntly produced. Ocelli near lateral margins of vertex, distance between eye and ocellus2.6x diameter of ocellus(
<figureCitation box="[243,317,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 45" captionStartId="4.[157,270,1416,1439]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,212,1389]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1395]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 45. Head &amp; pronotum Sophonia species 31. S. bakeri Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 32. S. bifida Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 33. S. chandrai Meshram &amp; Ramamurthy; 34. S. complexa Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 35. S. complicata Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 36. S. illuminata (Distant); 37. S. insignis Distant 38. S. intricata sp. nov.; 39. S. keralica Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 40. S. linealis (Distant); 41. S. longicephala (Ahmed &amp; Mahmood); 42. S. longitudinalis (Distant); 43. S. modesta (Distant); 44. S. tridenta sp. nov.; 45. S. vidarvya sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400215/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">Fig.44</figureCitation>
). Vertex broadly concave and punctuate. Scutellum as long as pronotum, Pronotum 0.7x longer than broad and as long asvertex (
<figureCitation box="[465,549,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 45" captionStartId="4.[157,270,1416,1439]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,212,1389]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1395]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 45. Head &amp; pronotum Sophonia species 31. S. bakeri Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 32. S. bifida Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 33. S. chandrai Meshram &amp; Ramamurthy; 34. S. complexa Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 35. S. complicata Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 36. S. illuminata (Distant); 37. S. insignis Distant 38. S. intricata sp. nov.; 39. S. keralica Viraktamath &amp; Wesley; 40. S. linealis (Distant); 41. S. longicephala (Ahmed &amp; Mahmood); 42. S. longitudinalis (Distant); 43. S. modesta (Distant); 44. S. tridenta sp. nov.; 45. S. vidarvya sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400215/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400217/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="584" targetBox="[156,1431,556,1870]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1899,1952]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,343,1899,1922]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">FIGURES 53–59.</emphasis>
Genitalia male 
<taxonomicName box="[513,698,1900,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sophonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridenta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[513,698,1900,1922]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">Sophonia tridenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[708,792,1900,1921]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[708,792,1900,1921]" pageId="7" pageNumber="584" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
53. Male genitalia; 54. Pygofer process; 55. Connective; 56. Style; 57, 58. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 59. Subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">
Male genitalia. Pygofer suboval, with several macrosetae in posterior half, ventral process long, pointed apically with subapical spinelike tridentate process below which single toothlike spine arises (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1424,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1899,1922]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,556,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,551,1878]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Genitalia male Sophonia tridenta sp. nov. 53. Male genitalia; 54. Pygofer process; 55. Connective; 56. Style; 57, 58. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 59. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400217/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">Figs. 53–54</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate broader medially than at apex and base with median row of six stout macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[1273,1358,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1899,1922]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,556,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,551,1878]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Genitalia male Sophonia tridenta sp. nov. 53. Male genitalia; 54. Pygofer process; 55. Connective; 56. Style; 57, 58. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 59. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400217/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Style withshort preapical lobe, apophysis short, apex short, beaklike (
<figureCitation box="[886,974,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1899,1922]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,556,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,551,1878]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Genitalia male Sophonia tridenta sp. nov. 53. Male genitalia; 54. Pygofer process; 55. Connective; 56. Style; 57, 58. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 59. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400217/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped with stem 
<date box="[1369,1403,260,284]" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">3X</date>
as long as arms, apex expanded (
<figureCitation box="[520,597,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1899,1922]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,556,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,551,1878]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Genitalia male Sophonia tridenta sp. nov. 53. Male genitalia; 54. Pygofer process; 55. Connective; 56. Style; 57, 58. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 59. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400217/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">Fig.55</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with dorsal apodome elongated, slender, dorsally directed, without processes; shaft tubular, dorsoanteriorly curved with pair of long, straight processes arising at base and extended posterodorsad, pair of slender subapical processes directed caudally, each with spine near midlength laterally, apex of shaft with membranous elongated structure (
<figureCitation box="[844,971,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 53 – 59" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1899,1922]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,556,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,551,1878]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 53 – 59. Genitalia male Sophonia tridenta sp. nov. 53. Male genitalia; 54. Pygofer process; 55. Connective; 56. Style; 57, 58. Aedeagus, lateral &amp; caudal view; 59. Subgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/400217/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">Fig. 57–58</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,717]" box="[199,1424,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,439,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="585">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 
<quantity box="[452,538,440,464]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="585" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[609,695,440,464]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="585" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes, 
<quantity box="[904,990,440,464]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="585" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
wide across hind margin of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
